{
  "title": "IELTS · Clean Water as a Basic Right",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "虽然清洁水对人类生存至关重要，应被认定为基本权利，但我并不认为这自动意味着家庭用水应完全免费。",
      "phrases": ["While clean water", "is undoubtedly essential", "for human survival", "and should be recognised", "as a fundamental right,", "I do not believe", "this automatically means", "households should receive it", "completely free of charge."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "在我看来，政府应保证基本用水免费，超出部分收费。",
      "phrases": ["In my view,", "governments should guarantee", "a basic amount of water", "for free,", "but charge", "for any usage beyond that."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "支持免费供水的人有令人信服的道德理由。",
      "phrases": ["Those who support", "free water supply", "have a compelling moral case."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "没人应该因为付不起钱就被拒之门外；在许多发展中地区，家庭仍要步行数小时从不安全水源取水。",
      "phrases": ["No one should be denied water", "simply because", "they cannot afford it,", "and in many developing regions,", "families still walk for hours", "to fetch water", "from unsafe sources."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "让水免费将确保即便是最贫困的公民也能维持卫生、做饭、保持健康。",
      "phrases": ["Making water free", "would ensure that", "even the poorest citizens", "can maintain hygiene,", "cook meals,", "and stay healthy."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这也会减少霍乱等水传播疾病的扩散，这些疾病在非洲和南亚部分地区仍是严重的公共卫生威胁。",
      "phrases": ["This would also reduce", "the spread of", "waterborne diseases", "such as cholera,", "which remains a serious", "public health threat", "in parts of Africa and South Asia."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "然而，把水完全免费会带来严重问题。",
      "phrases": ["However,", "treating water as entirely free", "would create significant problems."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "首先，净化、储存、输送到每家每户的成本极高。",
      "phrases": ["First,", "purifying, storing,", "and delivering water to every home", "is extremely expensive."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "管道、水处理厂和维护的成本必须有人承担；如果用户不付费，负担就全落在纳税人或政府预算上。",
      "phrases": ["The costs of pipelines,", "treatment plants,", "and maintenance", "must be covered by someone,", "and if users pay nothing,", "the burden falls entirely", "on taxpayers", "or the government budget."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "其次，免费用水往往鼓励浪费。",
      "phrases": ["Second,", "free water tends to", "encourage waste."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "当人们觉得资源没价值时，就更可能让水龙头开着、过度浇灌花园、或对漏水的管子视而不见。",
      "phrases": ["When people feel", "a resource has no value,", "they are far more likely", "to leave taps running,", "overwater their gardens,", "or ignore leaking pipes."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "像中国这样北方有上亿人口面临水资源短缺的国家，这种行为将是灾难性的。",
      "phrases": ["In countries like China,", "where water shortages", "affect hundreds of millions", "of people in the north,", "such behaviour would be disastrous."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "更平衡的方案是阶梯价格制。",
      "phrases": ["A more balanced solution", "is a tiered pricing system."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "每家可获得免费基础配额——足够饮用、做饭、清洗——而用量大的用户则支付逐级上涨的费率。",
      "phrases": ["Each household could receive", "a free basic quota —", "enough for drinking,", "cooking, and washing —", "while heavier users", "pay progressively higher rates."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "这种方式保护了穷人，反映了水的真实价值，并鼓励所有人负责任地使用。",
      "phrases": ["This approach", "protects the poor,", "reflects water's true value,", "and encourages everyone", "to use it responsibly."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "综上，虽然获得清洁水是基本权利，但完全免费既不实际也不明智。",
      "phrases": ["In conclusion,", "although access to clean water", "is a basic right,", "providing it entirely free of charge", "is neither practical nor wise."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "保证免费的最低供应，同时对额外用量收费，是更公平、更可持续的政策。",
      "phrases": ["Guaranteeing a free minimum supply", "while charging for additional use", "is a fairer", "and more sustainable policy."]
    }
  ]
}
